The reasoning and explanation behind just a few decisions got really long so this is part one.
I think she'd probably be a fairly powerful one and very much in contact with the outside world. One thing I would like to do would have her, and actually plenty of kitsunes for that matter, have been pseudo-enlisted to help with the war effort. Since kitsunes, especially the more powerful ones, are known for having extremely good senses their ability to gather accurate information would be absolutely invaluable. Naturally, that seems to conflict with things still going the way they did in our world. However, that's not factoring in one big reason why the Japanese lost: stubbornness and unwillingness to adapt. There were many, many times where Japanese officers, commanders, generals, admirals, etc. received new information that was vital to making a correct decision yet they simply refused to change from the course they had already plotted based upon poor information. However, that doesn't cover everything. There were plenty of times where information almost certainly would have shifted the battle, perhaps most notably among them being Midway and Guadalcanal.

And part two.
